            },
            "answer_text": "Some of them were. Most Mongols were Tengrists, followers of the native shamanistic religion of the steppes. However, some were not. There were some Buddhists, a few Muslims, and some Christians. Notably, the Keralites, one of the major tribes comprising Genghis\u2019s Mongol confederation, were predominantly Nestorian Christians. Christianity got a bit of a boost in the east as Nestorian Mongols were able to use their influence within the religiously pluralistic Mongol empire to spread their religion and limit the spread of others in limited ways. ",
